## âš™ï¸ Installation & Setup

1. **Clone the Repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/purohitharshita/offline-harassment-detection.git
cd offline-harassment-detection

2. **Create Virtual Environment**
```bash
python -m venv myenv
# Activate Virtual Environment
source myenv/bin/activate     # Linux/Mac
myenv\Scripts\activate        # Windows

3. **Install Dependencies**
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. **Run the Application**
```bash
streamlit run ui.py

## ğŸ“Š Datasets

- **Video Dataset:** [Real-Life Violence Situations (RLVS)](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mohamedmustafa/real-life-violence-situations-dataset) â€” contains approximately 2,000 video clips, evenly split between violent and non-violent situations, collected from real-life scenarios :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}.  
- **Audio Dataset:** [RAVDESS Emotional Speech Audio](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uwrfkaggler/ravdess-emotional-speech-audio) â€” high-quality emotional speech recordings covering emotions like calm, happy, sad, angry, fearful, surprised, and disgusted at two intensity levels :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=1}.

âš ï¸ *Datasets are **not included** in this repository due to size. Please download them separately from the links provided and place them in the `data/` folder.*


